## Context

- Run 9: literature searches across all 7 active initiatives (all in development) + follow-up on run 8 items
- Created journal entry #1120 with 6 findings + negative results
- Created 3 tasks: research_director #816 (Han VX published scRNA-seq findings for IVIG project, P5), #817 (PANDAS vs PANS stratification + NfL biomarker for transcriptomic panel, P4), #818 (JAK/STAT targetable node + oxidative stress for cytokine network, P3)
- MAJOR: Han VX et al. scRNA-seq paper PUBLISHED (PMID 40953324, Neurology N&NI Nov 2025). 144,470 cells, 11 clusters, pre-IVIG PANS = downregulated immune pathways + aberrant NK cells, post-IVIG = reversed + histone modification pathways downregulated in neutrophils/NK cells. Authors propose PANS = epigenetic immune brain disorder. GEO data STILL NOT deposited.
- Totè et al. 2025 (PMID 40650125): PANDAS ≠ PANS biochemically. PANDAS has elevated sNOX2-dp, isoprostanes, LPS, zonulin. PANS = controls. Gut barrier permeability implicated in PANDAS.
- Hargarten et al. 2025 (PMID 40117367, Science Advances): Ruxolitinib first-in-human for neuroinflammation (cPIIRS). JAK/STAT dominant. 6 patients, tolerable, reduced markers. Validates Gorin IFNγ reversibility via JAK inhibition.
- NfL biomarker: Mazowiecki 2024 (PMID 39715492, 104 pediatric anti-NMDAR: NfL OR 3.62, combined AUC 0.836) + Businaro 2025 (PMID 40561419, CASPR2/LGI1: NfL predicts cognitive outcomes). No PANS/PANDAS NfL study yet = opportunity.
- Turowski 2025 (PMID 40407889): EMTICS underpowered for PANS/PANDAS (need ~14 cohorts for 1 patient). Being misused to deny IVIG. Strengthens biomarker urgency.
- Kumar et al. 2025 (bioRxiv): S. pyogenes factor H recruitment crystal structures (M5, M6, FbaA). FbaA in ~50% strains, conserved binding residues. Complement evasion relevant to GAS mimicry.
- Melamed et al. 2024 (PMID 39421743): IVIG response in PANS = reduced pro-inflammatory monocytes/DCs. 10 patients, all psychometric measures improved.
